Garry Monk is ready to take his place in the 'madhouse' after being appointed as manager of Barclays Premier League club Swansea.

Monk has spoken with several of his new managerial colleagues in English football's top flight after landing a three-year contract at the Liberty Stadium.

'A lot of them said "welcome to the madhouse". In fact, pretty much every one of them has said that,' said Monk, who revealed via his Twitter account on Friday night that he had officially retired as a player.

